
	<sn><md>## Viewing Changes Across Commits{.text-center}

When working with Git, it’s often necessary to compare two different commits to understand what has changed in the codebase. Git provides powerful options with the `git diff` command to view these changes in detail.

### Comparing Two Commits

The general syntax is:

```bash
git diff commit1 commit2
```

This shows the line-by-line differences between two commits.
